49 SECTION 2.
50 Said article is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
51 "37-2-12.
52 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
53 (1) 'Health care provider' means any health care professional licensed under Title 43 or
54 any hospital or other health care facility licensed or regulated under Chapter 7 of Title 31
55 or under this title.
56 (2) 'Panel' means the parity compliance review panel established pursuant to this Code
57 section.
58 (b) There is established a parity compliance review panel within the council to be
59 composed of:
60 (1) The following members of the council:
61 (A) The commissioner of community health, or his or her designee;
62 (B) The commissioner of behavioral health and developmental disabilities, or his or her
63 designee;
64 (C) The commissioner of human services, or his or her designee; and
65 (D) The Insurance Commissioner, or his or her designee; and
66 (2) The following appointed members:
67 (A) Two mental health clinicians, appointed by the Governor;
68 (B) Two senior executives of facilities or systems providing mental health care,
69 appointed by the Governor;
